  "text": "Here we are going to recall the notion of a semijective resolution from [CITATION_1] . By a resolution of a module M, we as usual mean a complex S whose cohomology H (S ) is identified with M[0], which denotes the complex ! 0 ! M ! 0 ! with M placed in degree 0. A semijective complex is a complex S of g-modules, such that (1) it is K-injective as a complex of g + -modules, i.e., for every acyclic complex A of g + -modules, Hom K(g + ) (A , S ) = 0, where K(g + ) is the homotopy category of complexes of g + -modules;",
